      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EYE KEEP SMILING (7) was far from disgraced when midfield against the boys in a Miracle Mile qualifier last week. She'll enjoy the return to her own sex having placed against the mares in her other three starts this time in, coming from the back row for third to the flying Captains Mistress in the G1 Queen of the Pacific two back. Has a terrific strike rate at this circuit and distance so can return to the winners' list. TOKYO ROSE NZ (6) wasn't too far off EYE KEEP SMILING when fourth in the Queen of the Pacific in their only clash. She has won her other three Australian starts, all of them at this circuit and distance and by big margins. Huge danger. THE VICAR OF DIBLEY NZ (5) was hampered by a flat tyre here last start so can do better. Big class jump for FARFALLA STRIDE (3) but she is in form with back-to-back wins and strikes at 50 per cent at this circuit and distance.",
